   <text>
      <body>

         <pb n="1r" facs="lf_pDas_1644_brd_16.jpg"/>

         <div xml:id="orig_div1" xml:lang="ara" type="invocation" rend="top centre">
            <p>
               <unclear>هو</unclear>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div corresp="#orig_div1" xml:id="trans_div1">
            <p>
               <unclear>He [God] is</unclear>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div2" xml:lang="per" type="maintext">
            <p> <lb/>زبده الاقران چودری
               <persName ref="#purshottamDas">پرشوتم داس</persName>
               و چودری
               <persName ref="#parasRam">پرسرام</persName>
                بعافیت باشد
               <lb/> هرچه گردید از خدا بباید الحال باز سیاهه روزنامچه و آمدن
               <lb/> و جمع و جمیع و رشته را
               <app>
                  <rdg cert="medium">درست</rdg>
                  <rdg cert="medium">دربست</rdg>
               </app>
               نموده بزودی زود بفرستد
               <lb/> درین باب تغافل نکنند که از این نوشته ها و سیاهه
               <lb/> اصلا و مطلقا در پیش فقیر نیست و نویسنده ها خود همه در خانه
               <lb/>خود مانند شما این قدر کار نکنید تنهای که نصفا نصف
               <lb/>نوشته بودید 
                  <unclear>مهر امل</unclear><note>a possible misspelling of عامل</note>            
                نموده حواله
               <unclear>باله</unclear>
                نموده چون در کنار
               <lb/>
               آب  شنیده شد
                که کس
                <persName ref="#narainModi">نراین مودی</persName>
               <unclear>گریخته</unclear>
                رفت
               <lb/>باز بهمین سبب همه دلگیر شده این ها را نگاهداشتند
               <lb/> هرکسی بیاید فرستاده خواهد شد اگر از 
               <placeName ref="#gujarat">گجرات</placeName>
               کسی آمده باشد
               <lb/> خبر آنجا را بنویسند و شخصی که از
               <placeName ref="#gujarat">گجرات</placeName>
               بیاید
               <note>From this line onwards, the text continues on the right margin of the
                  document.</note>
               <lb/> روانه اینجانب نمایند تغافل نکنند
               <lb/> اگر از
               <placeName ref="#ujjain">اوجین</placeName>
               خبر برسد بنویسند
               <lb/> تغافل نکنند و
               <gap/>
            </p>
         </div>

         <div corresp="#orig_div2" xml:id="trans_div2">
            <p> <lb/>Eminent among Contemporaries <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_chaudhri"
                  >chaudhri</ref>
               <persName ref="#purshottamDas">Purshottam Das</persName>
                and <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_chaudhri">chaudhri</ref>
               <persName ref="#parasRam">Paras Ram</persName>, may they [i.e. you] be well.
               <lb/> Whatever happens, [it] must come from [must have been ordained by] God. Now, once again, prepare the list of daily accounts
               <!--<note>Since siyahat indicates travel, in the overall context of the document, siyahat-i roznamche has been read as the despatch of daily accounts.</note>ET: changed translation to list; not sure this note is necessary given use of siyaha for account book, list, inventory, etc</-->
                  and arrivals and
              <lb/>tax collections and records and send them as soon as possible.
               <lb/> Do not neglect this since none of these notes and lists
               <lb/> in their original and entirety are in front of this poor man [me], and his [my] own records are at home.
               <lb/> You just do not work in such a way that you write in halves [i.e. vaguely].
               <lb/><unclear>Attach the official seal [to the papers]</unclear>
               [and] deposit them.<note>Literally, place them in a bag.</note>
               <lb/>
               Since it was heard at the edge of the water<note>This is likely an idiomatic expression</note> that some person <persName ref="#narainModi">Narain Modi</persName> <unclear>fled</unclear>
               <lb/><gap/>An eye should be kept on things
               <lb/> and whoever comes, should be sent. If anyone comes from <placeName ref="#gujarat">Gujarat</placeName>
               <lb/> with news from there, write [about it].
               <lb/> And if anybody comes from <placeName ref="#gujarat">Gujarat</placeName>, send them here.
               <lb/> If any news arrives from <placeName ref="#ujjain">Ujjain</placeName>, write.
               <lb/> Do not neglect it.
               <gap/>
            </p>
         </div>

         <div xml:id="orig_div3" xml:lang="per" type="authorisation" rend="right margin">
            <p><stamp type="seal"><mentioned>
                     <persName ref="#abdusSalam">عبد السلام</persName>
                      بن
                     <unclear>محمد</unclear>
                     <gap/>
                      خان
                     <gap/>
                      بنده سلطان
                     <persName ref="#muradBakhsh">مراد بخش</persName>
                      شهان
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">۱۰۵۴</date>
                  </mentioned></stamp>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div corresp="#orig_div3" xml:id="trans_div3">
            <p><stamp type="seal">Round black ink seal<mentioned>
                     <persName ref="#abdusSalam">Abdussalam</persName>
                      son of <unclear>Muhammad</unclear>
                     <gap/> Khan
                      servant of Sultan
                     <persName ref="#muradBakhsh">Murad Bakhsh</persName>
                     <gap/>
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">1054</date>
            </mentioned></stamp><note>It appears that the seal was applied after concluding the main text in the
               right margin. While a date has been ascribed to the document based on the year in the seal, it was likely issued in the mid-1650s. <persName ref="#abdusSalam">Abdussalam></persName>
               used the same seal in 1655, in the document "<ref type="document" target="#lf_pDas_1655_brd_ac">Order of Abdussalam to Purshottam Das and Paras Ram about a dispute with
                  other officials</ref>".</note></p>
         </div>
      </body>
